summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 4366, entitled "An Ordinance providing for licensing and regulating the peddling and hawking of meat, game, poultry, fruit, vegetables, butter, eggs, and other farm and dairy produce, other than milk, within the City of Seattle, repealing all ordinances in conflict or inconsistent therewith, and providing penalties for the violation thereof", approved December 9, 1896.
